Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.71,0:00:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And today, carrying the weight of nuclear fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.13,0:00:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we find the star that, in faraway outer space,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.54,0:00:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,keeps burning fiercely in order to support life:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.38,0:00:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.88,0:00:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And under his highly elevated appearance...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.98,0:00:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,DON'T FUCK WITH ME!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.48,0:00:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,DON'T FUCK WITH MEEEEE!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.20,0:00:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ostrich belongs to the species Struthio\Ncamelus of the family Struthionidae.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.83,0:00:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Height: 2.15 m, weight: 115 kg,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.00,0:00:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,total cubic displacement: 5000 cc,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.71,0:00:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maximum power: 3500 ps gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.54,0:00:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its maximum running speed is 60 km/h.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.42,0:00:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of all the existing ratites,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.09,0:00:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the ostrich is considered the largest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.35,0:01:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this bird,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.31,0:01:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Aristotle called the "Libyan sparrow,"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.43,0:01:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,feeds himself by stealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.65,0:01:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's also well known for his shameful habit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.40,0:01:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of hiding his head while exposing his butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.03,0:01:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But all of these rumors are of course nothing but lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.03,0:01:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.37,0:01:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, our ostrich, together with his children,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.38,0:01:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,travels lightheartedly through the map, when at\Nsome point he encounters another little family.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.50,0:01:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's going to happen next?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.42,0:01:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Name: Ostrich A HP: 1089 MP: 372
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.59,0:01:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ostrich B and his children appear!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.80,0:01:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a9}Attack Method\NMagic Items\NDefense Run
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.34,0:01:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a9}Claws\NWeapon\NTabara\NItsuki\NRhythm
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.18,0:01:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a9}Pot\NBoiler\NFridge
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.72,0:01:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ostrich A rows a pot!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.64,0:01:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wonderful headshot on Ostrich B.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.60,0:01:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Ostrich B's turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.81,0:01:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ostrich A escapes quick as an ostrich.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.06,0:01:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ostrich B totters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.35,0:01:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an opening!!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.31,0:01:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a9}Attack Method\NMagic Items\NDefense Run
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a9}Ostrich ray\NOstrich special\N20 mon\N40 mon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ostrich A launches a fatal shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.81,0:01:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ostrich B is KO'd.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.98,0:01:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ostrich B had four children.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.31,0:01:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Level: 63 EX: 1201335
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.36,0:01:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After this last bloody fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.65,0:01:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the winning parent adopts the loser's children
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.36,0:01:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and raises them as if they were his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.82,0:02:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the big secret in the world of birds!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.28,0:02:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There's no treasure more precious than sons."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.58,0:02:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A son is worth more than a thousand garnets."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.29,0:02:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Three daughters are worth a fortune."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.96,0:02:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you really have to be a dog, be a dog in a large family."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.87,0:02:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in spite of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.58,0:02:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine the pain of a father
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.38,0:02:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who sees his children taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.88,0:02:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the story of a severe, too severe\Nostrich, ready to steal his kin's children,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.80,0:02:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even in a hostile environment that\Ndoesn't easily support sons!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.28,0:02:45.66,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,I watch the sky through the keyhole, and\Nwhat I see is a person's silhouette
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.45,0:02:52.33,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my casual encounter with a tomorrow I've never seen
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.67,0:02:58.21,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Outer space always starts from an interphone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.88,0:03:04.72,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, one step out, and I find the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.01,0:03:10.60,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no armor to protect the family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:17.98,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The only weapon to search for our roots is consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.36,0:03:27.83,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had love, dreams, and frontiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.79,0:03:39.63,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Lineage, the road home, heritage, and\Norigins depend on space and time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.13,0:03:47.89,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The wife has the household, the servant, and the genealogy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.10,0:03:53.02,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Transcend and run through the time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:03:59.19,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Long long life to the ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.99,0:04:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oarai Beach. Oarai Beach."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.18,0:06:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:36.38,stop2,,0000,0000,0000,,Next stop is Arai Misaki
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:36.38,stop1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oarai Sea Baths Station
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.89,0:06:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.86,0:06:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Guard Dog of Time" by Murota Bunmei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.95,0:06:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Always waiting for dawn,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:07:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}until the battle of time reaches its end.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.21,0:07:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His "black list" includes the Bible.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anarchy is his faith.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.47,0:07:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And he'll kill those who oppose him without mercy!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.44,0:07:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Groping in the dark, with his back to the wall...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.49,0:07:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An unsinkable aircraft carrier, redeemer of his own name...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.95,0:07:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A tax deduction, a man overwhelming to women...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.58,0:07:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}May 3rd, useless and bulky stuff.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.05,0:07:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, what loneliness!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.98,0:08:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A guard dog lost in the wind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.57,0:08:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}barks in the middle of his confused thoughts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.03,0:08:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A fascism called freedom,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.75,0:08:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}a nihilism that finds shelter in peace...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.08,0:08:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's what the dog is smelling,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.76,0:08:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}together with mendacious orders.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Declarations of war and mass blitzes,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.06,0:08:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}light speed and perestroika,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.52,0:08:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}hard lines and liver malfunctions,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:09:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sunday holidays and Arima hotsprings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.08,0:09:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, such sad things...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.28,0:09:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.36,0:09:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.20,0:09:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.08,0:09:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.25,0:09:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.88,0:09:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko! Maroko! Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.21,0:09:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.34,0:09:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.76,0:10:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the corncobs are burned!\NWe have to sell them, understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.06,0:10:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we roasting this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.81,0:10:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who'll eat it are stray dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.77,0:10:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll never get any customers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if there are customers or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or if the consumer of the corncobs is a man or a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's none of your business anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.86,0:10:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got that, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father took out a loan of five million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, I'd just have slapped that girl in some dive,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.29,0:10:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I accepted your offer to work in her place,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.37,0:10:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to pay me back at least the interest!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm allowing you to do that by making you work
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.79,0:10:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the company kiosk!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.25,0:10:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think carefully before you complain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.63,0:10:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't spare any effort!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.43,0:10:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.76,0:10:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think that if I worked harder,\Ncustomers would come?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.18,0:10:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I work harder, will someone show up?!\NWill something happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I'm bearing the handicap of a gloomy thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.06,0:10:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that is, the need to repay my father's debt,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.32,0:10:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to the edge of a beach far away from the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.03,0:11:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,hoping that this would bring new developments
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the story of Maroko and me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.83,0:11:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to find a hip job,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.16,0:11:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one that would've paid me enough to live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.21,0:11:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our summer days would've been moistened with sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once gone, Inumaru's and Maroko's\N17th summer will never return again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that at least I could avoid the bleak\Ndrama of a young girl working in a dive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.47,0:11:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and of a young man who lives off her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.93,0:11:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came here believing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.02,0:11:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of story begins, instead, with roasting corncobs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.48,0:11:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on a rusty grid by a booth stall that looks like a doghouse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.69,0:11:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsk!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.99,0:11:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The desire to look for a different story that\Nbegins with a revolutionary development,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ignited by a character appearing from\Nnowhere, or by a new situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.33,0:11:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in reality usurps the possibility of the story itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.75,0:11:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this antithesis is unintelligible to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.96,0:11:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The structure of a tale or story that has a beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.13,0:12:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,middle, and so-called inescapable end,\Ndoes nothing but depict itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It comes to be universally accepted\Nand thus known as a "great story"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.10,0:12:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only from this very aspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.26,0:12:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A tale worthy to be called that has\Nno beginning, or middle, or end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.69,0:12:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.27,0:12:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The infinite repetition of inescapable logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.86,0:12:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If on this desolate beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.49,0:12:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in this abandoned doghouse in the middle of the desert,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.57,0:12:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in this dive where we senselessly keep on roasting corncobs\Nfor customers who will probably never come;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.49,0:12:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in other words, if in this very moment,\Nyou cannot foresee your possible story,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.37,0:12:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,well then, this now is the end of your story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if by some chance customers should arrive,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.17,0:12:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this would only be evidence\Nthat confirms the loop of the same logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.46,0:12:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on what basis should I play the role of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.56,0:12:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's as easy as could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.81,0:12:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring to a more dramatic story
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.06,0:12:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is your specialty, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.48,0:13:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And after all, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.65,0:13:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.82,0:13:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Customers are coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.24,0:13:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemon shaved ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.70,0:13:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather, a lemon shaved ice, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.83,0:13:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lemonade!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.33,0:13:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.13,0:13:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't offend my grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.17,0:13:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.17,0:13:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Maroko, I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.05,0:13:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.34,0:13:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a wonderful little place! Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.14,0:13:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world are you doing? Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.22,0:13:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.35,0:13:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.36,0:13:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the famous Oarai Beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.40,0:13:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This beach was considered a mecca for families,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.86,0:13:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the legendary shore where once fragmented\Nfamilies finally found harmony again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.83,0:13:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the famous Oarai Beach, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.41,0:13:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, aren't you mistaking this for a totally different place?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No customer would bother coming\Nto this God-forsaken beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.92,0:14:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only creatures that come to visit are schools of jellyfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.05,0:14:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the memories of the families that used\Nto meet here end up shattered on the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.18,0:14:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On this beach, the only thing left to do is to wait for death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.02,0:14:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.73,0:14:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should not be any mistake, should there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.10,0:14:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.73,0:14:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that man standing over there pretending\Nto be a passer-by... darling!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.15,0:14:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.24,0:14:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}12
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.24,0:14:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}11
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.24,0:14:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}10
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.99,0:14:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tamiko, your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}9
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.53,0:14:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Ignition.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.99,0:14:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tamiko, your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.75,0:14:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}6
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.50,0:14:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}5
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.58,0:14:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.37,0:14:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}4
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.54,0:14:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,re-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}3
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.75,0:14:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.29,0:14:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}2
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.87,0:14:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,am-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.42,0:14:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}1
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.62,0:14:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,back home!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.97,0:14:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, moron?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.23,0:15:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.90,0:15:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whisper of the past that the sea\Nimparts to us from its depths.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.95,0:15:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like waves that shatter and then retire:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.45,0:15:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's the story of an unhappy family
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.03,0:15:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sunk in the adversity of the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.87,0:15:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a faded color film that brings back our memories,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.92,0:15:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or like a scene from childhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.54,0:15:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whose brightness has never been scratched\Nbut rather transfigured by life,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.34,0:15:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or like a couple now tired of being together,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.80,0:15:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on a night that recalls the excited heartbeats\Nof their first encounter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.52,0:15:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe memories of summer days
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are also carved in that family's story,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.73,0:15:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,full of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the dazzling light of the sun's rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.19,0:15:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a little son plays vivaciously, screaming in a shrill voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.49,0:15:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under a parasol, opened in the shape of a flower,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the father answers with a laugh, in his virile voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.16,0:16:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The young wife pours her husband tea,\Nkept fresh in a thermos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All this, without ever imagining the father-son conflicts,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.54,0:16:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the marital boredom that will probably arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.13,0:16:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hundred,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.05,0:16:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a thousand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ten thousand times...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.63,0:16:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An infinite number of times it repeats,\Nwhenever summer returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.30,0:16:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Year after year, in summer, the picture\Nof the happy family renews itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.43,0:16:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This beach now repels visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sealed inside it are family pictures that\Nnow belong to the whispers of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.36,0:16:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a beach where the memories of\Na past in which the family was a family
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.82,0:16:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shatter and retire like waves on the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.15,0:16:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Oarai Beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.55,0:16:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.05,0:16:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you now, Inumaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.55,0:16:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.93,0:16:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look out of shape, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.89,0:16:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.97,0:17:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey. Are you done with your greetings?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.06,0:17:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be Mrs. Tamiko Yomota.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.73,0:17:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.48,0:17:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're from Yoshitomo Financial, Ltd.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.11,0:17:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Fumiaki Murota.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.20,0:17:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Set a thief to catch a thief," huh?\NI see you're well supported.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.16,0:17:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, you're saving me time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.62,0:17:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, at this moment your son Inumaru and this girl
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are actually my hostages.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.63,0:17:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To ransom them, all you have to\Ndo is to give me what's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about the girl. For now, I'll take back my son!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.97,0:17:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's with the intent of putting an end to this story
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.52,0:17:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I've come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.81,0:17:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, Tamiko, you must know that-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.69,0:17:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, you vile wretch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.61,0:17:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four months and two weeks have passed since I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But during that time, I have not been idle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:18:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have used every possible means to\Nopen your eyes, and your son's eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.33,0:18:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the shameless identity of that girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.37,0:18:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and reestablish order in the Yomota family!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.92,0:18:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now that I have returned expressly to obtain this result,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.13,0:18:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will {\i1}never{\i0} allow further dissolute\Ndevelopments like the ones up till now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.97,0:18:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, humble Yomota Tamiko, came\Nhere to make sure of the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.59,0:18:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to put an end to this situation, and to avoid further carnage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.57,0:18:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In May 1987, near Kobayakawa house at\NHachinoe in the province of Aomori,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.37,0:18:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a girl appeared who declared herself an illegitimate\Nelder sister of the sons of the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.87,0:18:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and settled down to live there ever after.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.25,0:18:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the 20th of the same month, she entered the\Nfamily as the adopted child of the younger son,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.96,0:18:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and one day, after a quarrel revolving\Naround Maroko, the parents and sons
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,separated, and divorce followed immediately thereafter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.26,0:19:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In July of the same year, the third son of that family
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.18,0:19:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ran away from home with the girl, and even now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.85,0:19:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is not known whether he's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.85,0:19:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In January 1988, in Fussa near Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.94,0:19:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the funeral of Nunoyama Yuji (42), a TV\Nproducer dead from cirrhosis of the liver,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.77,0:19:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a girl appeared who claimed to be\Nthe man's illegitimate daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.32,0:19:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,creating a scandal, and then she disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In March of the same year, at the house of Toboyama\NShigeo (38), an actor living in Nagoya,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.45,0:19:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where he was undergoing treatment for a\Nhypertrophied appendix, a girl appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.00,0:19:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who claimed to be his long lost,\Nnever-forgotten sweetheart from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.01,0:19:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man's real partner, who had\Nassisted him during treatment,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.13,0:19:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had a furious quarrel with this lover\Nwho had suddenly appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.14,0:19:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then, a victim of hypertension,\Ndeveloped an anal prolapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.02,0:19:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the last 40 days, he has lingered at\Nthe boundary between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.19,0:19:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,August of the same year, Kogura, Kyushu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.69,0:19:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,October, Ishigashima, in Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:20:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,November, Tomakomai, in Hokkaido.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.03,0:20:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The following February, in the Japanese\Ndistrict of San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.30,0:20:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The places this mysterious girl visits
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.05,0:20:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,become whirlpools of lies and confusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.39,0:20:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The families that let her in, without exception,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.22,0:20:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,undergo bloody fights that wash blood with more blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.31,0:20:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Divorces, runaways, families destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.94,0:20:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In truth, she's nothing other than the essence\Nof deepest evil for the family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.40,0:20:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the enemy of the family, who spreads\Nthe seeds of contention and betrayal!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She conspires for the collapse of family order,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the eternal anarchist!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.53,0:20:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the true identity of this girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.25,0:20:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.00,0:20:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Maroko would never...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.17,0:20:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing but idle chatter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.71,0:20:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a conspiracy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.63,0:21:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember, you can talk only when\Nand if I give you permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.47,0:21:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to speak!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.39,0:21:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A swindler of blood relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.31,0:21:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A genius of family destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.44,0:21:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's your hypothesis, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.65,0:21:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.90,0:21:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man I happened to "shake hands" with,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that man who called himself Murota\NBunmei, who is he then?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.03,0:21:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you deny that Maroko is my granddaughter\Ncome from the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.45,0:21:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then ipso facto, you must you also deny
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.29,0:21:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he was a Time Patroller.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.59,0:21:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tatara Bannai.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.46,0:21:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.13,0:21:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man claimed he wanted to arrest this girl
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.22,0:21:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for having committed "crimes against time."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.55,0:21:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man called Muruto Bunmei
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.10,0:21:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is nothing more than her partner in crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The improbability of the premise that\Nshe really came from the future
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.69,0:22:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in a time machine creates instead a tangible\Ncontradiction and annihilates itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.03,0:22:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,hiding in this way its inherent improbability.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.32,0:22:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using an even more unreal situation\Nto distract from an unreal situation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.53,0:22:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the criminal technique known as masking,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.45,0:22:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as a cliche of every swindler.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.62,0:22:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof of their intention to conceal a fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.42,0:22:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, after investigating at Yoshimoto Financial, Ltd.,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.46,0:22:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I discovered evidence that no one named\NMurota Fumiaki works there,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.93,0:22:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and so I'm reporting this remarkable fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.60,0:22:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You who are observing the time pass. You!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.64,0:22:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, none other than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.15,0:22:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yomota Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.52,0:22:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.61,0:22:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the sequence of facts narrated up till now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.73,0:22:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is nothing but a criminal farce staged by these two,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.41,0:22:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a mere fantasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.57,0:22:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then all of this is a detailed mise-en-scene
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.74,0:22:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,intended to bring destruction on my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.08,0:22:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why are the Yomotas reunited here on the stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.92,0:23:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and enjoying their brief encounter?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.09,0:23:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other worlds,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.13,0:23:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how did an action occur which allowed\Nthe family promise to be realized?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.42,0:23:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.76,0:23:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a contravention of their premeditated objective,\Nalso called a contradiction in terms!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.35,0:23:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha? What about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.52,0:23:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A conjecture in retrospect, nothing more!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.35,0:23:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I actually took part in the action,\Nas a character unforeseen by their script.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.44,0:23:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.23,0:23:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the intervention of an unforeseen factor...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.61,0:23:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.57,0:23:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we have a scene where only bit players appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.69,0:23:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.90,0:23:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.70,0:23:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it was so...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.32,0:23:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.11,0:23:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it was so, nothing would change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.08,0:23:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The current situation no longer represents\Nthe culmination of their plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.20,0:23:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the crime you described as the destruction of our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.96,0:23:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.42,0:23:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least try to think it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.17,0:23:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Maroko wasn't my granddaughter,\Nif she was a perfect stranger,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.63,0:23:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could approach her proudly,\Nas a man who wasn't a blood relative,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.22,0:23:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without shattering the family drama's fiercest taboo, incest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.89,0:23:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, it would be the love story of a man and a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.77,0:24:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Maroko and I were united,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.81,0:24:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a new story of a new family would begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.82,0:24:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So how could this be a scenario of family destruction?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.49,0:24:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.61,0:24:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.07,0:24:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko would also become the daughter-in-law\Nof that man, my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.79,0:24:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True, granddaughter and daughter-in-law\Nare not the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.37,0:24:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no arguing with the fact\Nthat they're both part of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.67,0:24:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, there's not even one reasonable\Nargument to oppose this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.80,0:24:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, who would be excluded from this story?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.01,0:24:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a silly story.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.64,0:24:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As of now, neither affirming nor denying\Nthe unrealistic existence of Maroko
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.89,0:24:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will change the only options left to you:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.19,0:24:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,either end your part and leave this stage,\Nor continue in a secondary role.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.86,0:24:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hunter has been hunted down at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.90,0:24:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're trapped in your own plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.32,0:24:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you deserve for having\Nintroduced an external character
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.79,0:25:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,into a tragic story that should have remained\Nentirely within the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.25,0:25:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.83,0:25:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the one who denied this kind of development.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.96,0:25:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, how could she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.51,0:25:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this story, which began with an enforced situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.84,0:25:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and has continuously stalled out,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.39,0:25:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could any other development ever exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.22,0:25:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.77,0:25:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You forgot about the existence of a very important character.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.15,0:25:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A certain character who continues to exist despite\Nyour chatter, which has excluded him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.07,0:25:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A character whose mere appearance on stage\Nwould shake this story to its foundations.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.99,0:25:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking so arrogantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.46,0:25:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.54,0:25:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name of this man is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.30,0:25:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Emergency announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.67,0:25:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Three days ago, August 15,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.88,0:25:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}at a Post Office on the periphery of Chiba,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.84,0:26:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}a middle-aged man broke in, armed\Nwith a metal-head driver,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.60,0:26:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}stole five million yen, and then vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.56,0:26:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The Chiba police department suspects an\Nunemployed man in trouble over debts,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.15,0:26:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Yomota Kinekuni, 48 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.90,0:26:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}We are looking for information about this man,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.24,0:26:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}and we have received a report that\Nhe may be near Oarai Beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.65,0:26:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.66,0:26:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must have spotted him coming\Nhere and reported it to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.95,0:26:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can we do? The patrol car is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.37,0:26:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's run, great-grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.75,0:26:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All together this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.17,0:26:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather Inumaru, great-grandmother, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.67,0:26:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.55,0:26:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.59,0:26:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.93,0:26:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't do anything else!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.39,0:26:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.10,0:26:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bit of a contrived {\i1}deus ex machina,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.35,0:26:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I guess it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.02,0:26:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.35,0:26:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we back to this conclusion now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.85,0:26:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What have we been talking about until now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.23,0:26:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, proceeding with such development
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.99,0:26:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,makes no sense at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.99,0:26:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.61,0:27:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's been no sense since the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.87,0:27:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.16,0:27:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.29,0:27:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're a family, that's why!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.37,0:27:28.35,Gosenzo,,0000,0000,0000,,Gosenzo-sama Banbanzai!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.68,0:27:35.07,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(200,425)\fad(500,800)}The Calm Before The Storm
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.99,0:27:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Opening Theme: "Gosenzosama Banbanzai!"\NLyrics and sing performace: Yumi Kojima\NSong production and arrangement: Kenji Kawai
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.22,0:28:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Marked now as a criminal organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.39,0:28:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Yomota family continues to hide away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.85,0:28:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With their backs to the wall, and misery in front of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.27,0:28:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this is way too miserable an end for their story.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.06,0:28:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time! Gosenzosama Banbanzai, episode 5:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.86,0:28:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One for All, All for One!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.36,0:29:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you next time!
